Class QVTRConfigurationJob

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:
de.uka.ipd.sdq.workflow.IBlackboardInteractingJob<de.uka.ipd.sdq.workflow.mdsd.blackboard.MDSDBlackboard>, de.uka.ipd.sdq.workflow.IJob
public class QVTRConfigurationJob
extends AbstractTransformationConfigurationJob

Configures a QVT-R transformation job. Most important, this includes the configuration of source and target models as well as the transformation script. Minor configuration settings include the location where tracing information are stored and the debug level of the QVT-R execution.

Version:
0.1
Author:
Kapova et al., Sebastian Lehrig (lehrig@mail.upb.de)

execute

public void execute(org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor monitor)
             throws de.uka.ipd.sdq.workflow.exceptions.JobFailedException,
                    de.uka.ipd.sdq.workflow.exceptions.UserCanceledException
Sets up the configuration for the QVT-R configuration object. For this, the method needs to access the work flow blackboard to receive the respective source and target models. Furthermore, the language configuration object gives the path to store tracing information and the location of the transformation script.
